<tr>
<td style="background:#4F4F4F" align="center"><b>Letter</b>
</td>
<td style="background:#4F4F4F" align="center"><b>Thought for the day</b>
</td>
<td style="background:#4F4F4F" align="center"><b>Source</b>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"><b>B</b>
</td>
<td align="center"><b>Be courageous and bold, be humble before your masters, lead with valour! These things above all others will be of use when your time comes to die.</b>
</td>
<td align="center"><a href="/wiki/Warhammer_40,000_3rd_Edition_Rulebook" title="Warhammer 40,000 3rd Edition Rulebook">Warhammer 40,000 3rd Edition Rulebook</a>, page 84
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align="center">
</td>
<td align="center"><b>Be grateful of your Master's favour!</b>
</td>
<td align="center"><a href="/wiki/Warhammer_40,000_4th_Edition_Rulebook" title="Warhammer 40,000 4th Edition Rulebook">Warhammer 40,000 4th Edition Rulebook</a>, page 238
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align="center">
</td>
<td align="center"><b>Be Pure.</b>
